{"lemma":"مُرَبَّعانِ","slug":"مُرَبَّعانِ","root":"ر.ب.ع","root_slug":"ر-ب-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ب-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14559","n14560","n14561","n14562","n14563"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"square, quadrangular piece"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"quartet"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"square, quadratic"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"fourfold, quadruple"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"tetragonal, quadrangular"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"meadow"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pasture"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of رَبَّعَ (rabbaʕa, “to quadruple”); compare أَرْبَعَة (ʔarbaʕa, “four”). Cognate with Aramaic מְרַבַע/ܡܪܒܥ (mrabbaˁ, mrubbaˁ, “square”).\n\nNoun of place from the verb رَبَعَ (rabaʕa, “to feed oneself in the pasture”), from a ر ب ع (r b ʕ) derived from رَبِيع (rabīʕ, “spring (season)”)."},"ipa":["/mu.rab.baʕ/"]}